</p>
<p>Challenges from Globalization, IMF Working Paper, 2009, p. 19), in sub-Saharan Africa between 
1980 and 2005, the proportion of countries providing incentives rose from 45 to 69 per cent. Effective 
corporate tax rates have dropped close to or even below zero in many developing countries (S. M. Ali 
Abbas and Alexander Klemm, A Partial Race to the Bottom: Corporate Tax Developments in 
Emerging and Developing Economies, IMF Working Paper, 2012, p. 9). 
</p>
<p> 
</p>
<p>84
